Comedian-cum-activist Mr Macaroni has explained why he is politically active. According to the popular skit maker, in an interview with Hip TV, the desire for change and the feeling of frustration from oppressions fuel his political activeness. He said: “I’m a Nigerian, I’m a Lagosian. I want things to be better. I’m tired and frustrated. Things have to change. If you want things to change you must come out.   DJ Sogood promises to dazzle Nigerians with new songs     Make Music Lagos returns for 2022 Edition     Alliance Française, Trace TV to celebrate World Music Day   “Nobody should stay back. If you have to talk from the back for things to change, you think the oppressors would listen? “No! They’ll continue to do things to frustrate and oppress you if you don’t use your voice to speak out. “So we must come out and show that we are ready.”